@page "/learn"
@layout Consensus.Web.Components.Layout.MainLayout

<PageTitle>Tutorials · Consensus Lab</PageTitle>

<div class="learn-home">
    <MudStack Spacing="2" Class="mb-6">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h3" Class="font-weight-bold">Blockchain Tutorials</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Color="Color.Default" Style="font-weight: 400; max-width: 60ch;">
            Plain-English guides to blockchain consensus, written for curious high-school students
            and anyone new to the field. Read, then jump into the simulator and watch the protocols
            play out on real nodes.
        </MudText>
    </MudStack>

    <MudPaper Elevation="0" Outlined="true" Class="pa-6 mb-6">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mb-3">What is a blockchain?</MudText>

        <p>
            A <strong>blockchain</strong> is a special kind of shared notebook. It doesn't live on
            one computer — instead, hundreds or thousands of computers (called <em>nodes</em>) all
            keep their own copy. Every page of the notebook records a list of recent transactions
            (who paid whom, how much) and is glued to the previous page using a cryptographic
            <em>hash</em> — basically, a digital fingerprint of the page before it.
        </p>

        <p>
            Each new page is called a <strong>block</strong>. Lining the blocks up in order, with
            each block fingerprinting the last, gives us a <strong>chain</strong> of blocks —
            hence, "blockchain". Once a block is in the chain, tampering with it would change its
            fingerprint, which would break the link to the next block, which would break the link
            to the block after that, and so on. So everyone watching the chain would notice
            instantly.
        </p>

        <div class="blockchain-svg-wrapper">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 720 140" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" role="img"
                 aria-label="Three blocks chained together. Each block has a number, a list of transactions, and a hash of the previous block.">
                <defs>
                    <linearGradient id="blkGrad" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
                        <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#1f7ad8"/>
                        <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#0a3d62"/>
                    </linearGradient>
                </defs>
                <g font-family="Inter, system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="11" fill="white">
                    <!-- Block 1 -->
                    <rect x="10" y="20" width="180" height="100" rx="10" fill="url(#blkGrad)"/>
                    <text x="100" y="42" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">Block #1</text>
                    <text x="100" y="62" text-anchor="middle">Prev hash: 0000…</text>
                    <text x="100" y="78" text-anchor="middle">Alice → Bob, 5</text>
                    <text x="100" y="92" text-anchor="middle">Carol → Dan, 2</text>
                    <text x="100" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-style="italic">Hash: 8f3a…</text>

                    <!-- Block 2 -->
                    <rect x="270" y="20" width="180" height="100" rx="10" fill="url(#blkGrad)"/>
                    <text x="360" y="42" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">Block #2</text>
                    <text x="360" y="62" text-anchor="middle">Prev hash: 8f3a…</text>
                    <text x="360" y="78" text-anchor="middle">Eve → Frank, 7</text>
                    <text x="360" y="92" text-anchor="middle">Bob → Alice, 1</text>
                    <text x="360" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-style="italic">Hash: c9b1…</text>

                    <!-- Block 3 -->
                    <rect x="530" y="20" width="180" height="100" rx="10" fill="url(#blkGrad)"/>
                    <text x="620" y="42" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">Block #3</text>
                    <text x="620" y="62" text-anchor="middle">Prev hash: c9b1…</text>
                    <text x="620" y="78" text-anchor="middle">Frank → Eve, 3</text>
                    <text x="620" y="92" text-anchor="middle">Dan → Carol, 4</text>
                    <text x="620" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-style="italic">Hash: 4e2d…</text>
                </g>

                <!-- Arrows -->
                <g stroke="#666" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow)">
                    <line x1="195" y1="70" x2="265" y2="70"/>
                    <line x1="455" y1="70" x2="525" y2="70"/>
                </g>
                <defs>
                    <marker id="arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                        <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="#666"/>
                    </marker>
                </defs>
            </svg>
            <div class="diagram-caption">
                Each block points to the previous one using its hash. Change any transaction and
                every following hash breaks.
            </div>
        </div>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-6 mb-3">What is "consensus"?</MudText>

        <p>
            If thousands of computers all keep their own copy of the notebook, who decides which
            page comes next? If two nodes write a different page at the same time, which one wins?
            That decision-making process is called <strong>consensus</strong> — agreeing, without
            a central boss, on the next block to add.
        </p>

        <p>
            Consensus has to work even when some nodes are slow, offline, broken, or actively
            <strong>malicious</strong> (lying on purpose). Different blockchains pick different
            strategies. The five most influential ones are below.
        </p>
    </MudPaper>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mb-4">Pick a protocol to learn about</MudText>

    <MudGrid>
        <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
            <MudCard Outlined="true" Class="protocol-card">
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center" Class="mb-2">
                        <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Memory" Color="Color.Warning" Size="Size.Large" />
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">Proof of Work</MudText>
                        <MudSpacer />
                        <MudChip T="string" Size="Size.Small" Color="Color.Info" Variant="Variant.Outlined">Beginner</MudChip>
                    </MudStack>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Default" Class="mb-3">
                        The original Bitcoin protocol. Computers race to solve a math puzzle —
                        whoever wins gets to write the next page.
                    </MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption">Used by: Bitcoin, Litecoin, Dogecoin</MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
                <MudCardActions>
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary"
                               EndIcon="@Icons.Material.Filled.ArrowForward"
                               Href="/learn/pow">Read the tutorial</MudButton>
                </MudCardActions>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
            <MudCard Outlined="true" Class="protocol-card">
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center" Class="mb-2">
                        <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.AccountBalance" Color="Color.Success" Size="Size.Large" />
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">Proof of Stake</MudText>
                        <MudSpacer />
                        <MudChip T="string" Size="Size.Small" Color="Color.Info" Variant="Variant.Outlined">Beginner</MudChip>
                    </MudStack>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Default" Class="mb-3">
                        Validators put money on the line. The protocol picks one at random,
                        weighted by how much they staked.
                    </MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption">Used by: Ethereum, Cardano, Polkadot</MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
                <MudCardActions>
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary"
                               EndIcon="@Icons.Material.Filled.ArrowForward"
                               Href="/learn/pos">Read the tutorial</MudButton>
                </MudCardActions>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
            <MudCard Outlined="true" Class="protocol-card">
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center" Class="mb-2">
                        <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Groups" Color="Color.Secondary" Size="Size.Large" />
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">Delegated Proof of Stake</MudText>
                        <MudSpacer />
                        <MudChip T="string" Size="Size.Small" Color="Color.Info" Variant="Variant.Outlined">Intermediate</MudChip>
                    </MudStack>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Default" Class="mb-3">
                        Like a representative democracy. Token holders vote for a small group of
                        delegates who take turns writing pages.
                    </MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption">Used by: EOS, TRON, BitShares</MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
                <MudCardActions>
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary"
                               EndIcon="@Icons.Material.Filled.ArrowForward"
                               Href="/learn/dpos">Read the tutorial</MudButton>
                </MudCardActions>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
            <MudCard Outlined="true" Class="protocol-card">
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center" Class="mb-2">
                        <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Verified" Color="Color.Info" Size="Size.Large" />
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">PBFT</MudText>
                        <MudSpacer />
                        <MudChip T="string" Size="Size.Small" Color="Color.Warning" Variant="Variant.Outlined">Advanced</MudChip>
                    </MudStack>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Default" Class="mb-3">
                        Practical Byzantine Fault Tolerance. Nodes vote in three rounds to agree on
                        every block, even with some liars in the group.
                    </MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption">Used by: Hyperledger Fabric, Tendermint</MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
                <MudCardActions>
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary"
                               EndIcon="@Icons.Material.Filled.ArrowForward"
                               Href="/learn/pbft">Read the tutorial</MudButton>
                </MudCardActions>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
            <MudCard Outlined="true" Class="protocol-card">
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center" Class="mb-2">
                        <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Schedule" Color="Color.Tertiary" Size="Size.Large" />
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">Proof of Elapsed Time</MudText>
                        <MudSpacer />
                        <MudChip T="string" Size="Size.Small" Color="Color.Warning" Variant="Variant.Outlined">Advanced</MudChip>
                    </MudStack>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Default" Class="mb-3">
                        Each computer rolls a fair "wait timer" inside a tamper-proof chip.
                        Whoever waits the shortest wins.
                    </MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption">Used by: Hyperledger Sawtooth (Intel)</MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
                <MudCardActions>
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary"
                               EndIcon="@Icons.Material.Filled.ArrowForward"
                               Href="/learn/poet">Read the tutorial</MudButton>
                </MudCardActions>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
            <MudCard Outlined="true" Class="protocol-card cta-card">
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center" Class="mb-2">
                        <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.PlayCircle" Color="Color.Primary" Size="Size.Large" />
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">Try it yourself</MudText>
                    </MudStack>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Default" Class="mb-3">
                        Once you've read a tutorial, jump into the simulator. Pick a protocol,
                        choose how many nodes, run it, and watch the blocks come in.
                    </MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
                <MudCardActions>
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Outlined" Color="Color.Primary"
                               EndIcon="@Icons.Material.Filled.ArrowForward"
                               Href="/simulations">Run a simulation</MudButton>
                </MudCardActions>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>
</div>

<style>
    .learn-home {
        max-width: 1100px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 1rem 0 3rem;
    }

    .learn-home .protocol-card {
        height: 100%;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
    }

    .learn-home .protocol-card .mud-card-content {
        flex-grow: 1;
    }

    .learn-home .blockchain-svg-wrapper {
        margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem;
    }

    .learn-home .blockchain-svg-wrapper svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        max-height: 200px;
    }

    .learn-home .diagram-caption {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--mud-palette-text-secondary);
        margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }

    .learn-home p {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.65;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
</style>
